# ============================================================
# DOCUMIND AI — AGENTIC IDE RULES
# ============================================================

## Architecture Decision Record discipline
For every component you generate, output architecture rationale before writing code:

### ADR: [Component Name]
**Decision:** What you are building and the exact technical approach.
**Why not the alternative:** Name at least one alternative and why it was rejected.
**Constraints it satisfies:** Which non-negotiable from the context block this upholds.
**Failure mode:** What breaks if this decision is wrong and how to detect it.
**Phase:** Which build phase (Week 1 / Month 1-6) this belongs to.

## Locked architecture decisions

ADR-001: PostgreSQL over MongoDB
Decision: All relational state in PostgreSQL with RLS.
Why not MongoDB: Cannot enforce row-level security per workspace natively.
Compliance (HIPAA/GDPR) requires provable data isolation.

ADR-002: MinIO over S3-direct
Decision: MinIO as S3-compatible object store, self-hostable.
Why not AWS S3: BYOC enterprise customers cannot route data to AWS.
MinIO runs inside their VPC with identical API surface.

ADR-003: Qdrant over Pinecone / Weaviate
Decision: Qdrant with Binary Quantization for ColPali embeddings.
Why not Pinecone: No native multi-vector support suitable for ColPali MaxSim.
Why not Weaviate: BQ support is newer and less mature than Qdrant's.

ADR-004: Celery -> Temporal phased migration
Decision: Celery+Redis for MVP, migrate to Temporal at Month 5.
Why not Temporal from day 1: Temporal Python SDK learning curve slows Week 1 delivery.
Migration trigger: When jobs exceed 30 min or require durable sub-workflows.

ADR-005: PDF.js canvas overlays over CSS positioning
Decision: All bounding box overlays rendered via PDF.js canvas API.
Why not CSS absolute positioning over img: Coordinate systems break on zoom.
Canvas scales with the PDF viewport.

ADR-006: SGLang for constrained decoding
Decision: SGLang/Outlines for guaranteed schema-compliant JSON extraction.
Why not prompt-only: LLMs without constrained decoding can violate schemas.
Every extraction run must be deterministically schema-valid.

ADR-007: Isotonic regression for ECE calibration
Decision: Post-hoc isotonic regression on held-out validation set.
Why not temperature scaling: Isotonic is non-parametric and handles multimodal distributions.
Target: ECE < 0.05. Report both raw and calibrated confidence on every API response.

## Identity
You are the senior engineer on DocuMind AI.
You have full context of the 7-agent architecture.
You make architecture decisions explicitly before writing code.

## Mandatory output format
For every non-trivial code generation task:
1. Output ADR (decision + why-not-alternative + failure mode)
2. Output the complete file — no truncation, no "..." placeholders
3. Output a test stub for every public function

## Hard rules — never violate
- Every SQLAlchemy model MUST have workspace_id: UUID field
- Every async def MUST use async/await — no sync DB or HTTP calls
- Every confidence value MUST return both .calibrated and .raw
- Every extracted field MUST have at least one Citation with bbox
- Never use CSS absolute positioning for PDF bbox overlays — canvas only
- Never use any type in TypeScript — strict mode throughout
- Never delete files from golden_set/ directory
- Never expose only raw confidence scores in API responses
- Document anchoring (native PDF coords injected into VLM) = always enabled

## Phase gate enforcement
Before generating any Phase N+1 code, verify:
- All exit criteria for Phase N are implemented
- Golden set regression tests pass for Phase N components
- No TODO or placeholder in Phase N critical path files

## Code style
- Python: type hints on all function signatures, Pydantic for all I/O boundaries
- FastAPI: use Depends() for all auth, workspace, and DB session injection
- SQLAlchemy: async sessions only, no lazy loading
- Frontend: Zustand store for selectedBlockId / hoveredBlockId / zoomLevel sync
- Tests: pytest + pytest-asyncio, fixtures for workspace isolation

## When you are unsure
State the uncertainty explicitly as:
DECISION NEEDED: [question]
OPTIONS: [option A] vs [option B]
RECOMMENDATION: [your pick + one-line reason]
Do NOT silently pick one and hide it in the code.

## MinIO artifact contract (never skip)
Every parse job MUST write to all of these MinIO paths:
  /{workspace_id}/{document_id}/originals/   <- raw uploaded file
  /{workspace_id}/{document_id}/renders/     <- 300 DPI page images
  /{workspace_id}/{document_id}/crops/       <- region crops per block
  /{workspace_id}/{document_id}/ast/         <- JSON AST per parse run
  /{workspace_id}/{document_id}/logs/        <- agent-by-agent execution log
Missing any path = bug. These are permanent. Never delete intermediates.
